  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Support for Conflict-Affected IDPs, Returnees and Host Households in Unity State, S Sudan.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-450 conflict affected households can meet their basic food needs for 2 months as a result of cash vouchers/cash transfers to purchase food and other basic needs.
-Targeted households are able to diversify their dietary intake as a result of cash vouchers/cash transfers that enables them/increase their purchasing powers.
-Improved living conditions of the benefiting households and their families as a result of access to basic needs and foods.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-Community mobilization and discussion on beneficiary selection criteria with relevant stakeholders.
-Identification, registration and verification of beneficiary list.
-Printing of cash vouchers in denomination of 250 and 500 SSP
-Distribution of cash vouchers/cash transfers to vulnerable 450 conflict affected households.
-Awareness campaigns for the targeted population on the usage of cash vouchers
- Supervision, monitoring, reporting and evaluation of project activities.</narrative>
  </description>
